        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Three giant centipede carcasses have wire springs that pull out and fling their sharpened legs around the room.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:nature|dc:23|name:Bend Carapace|traits:mechanical,trap] (trained) to bend the centipede carapace so the wire can't pull out any more legs, or @Check[type:thievery|dc:21|name:Cut Wires|traits:mechanical,trap] (expert) to cut the springy wires. After all three carcasses are disabled (regardless of the check used), the trap is deactivated. The trap automatically deactivates after 10 rounds.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 5
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> Each creature within 30 feet of a centipede carcass that hasn't been disabled takes [[/r {6d4}[piercing]]]{6d4 piercing damage} (@Check[type:reflex|dc:22|basic:true|name:Avoid Carapace Strike|traits:mechanical,trap] save).</p>"
